<TITLE> BSF kills one, wounds two in Chapai: BDR </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Chapainawabganj, Jan 7 (bdnews24.com) - Indian border guards gunned down one man and injured two others on Shibganj border in Chapainawabganj Tuesday night, a BDR official said. Major Syed Abu Hasan, operations officer of 39 Rifles Battalion said the casualties occurred when BSF members of Sukhdevpur camp opened fire on the residents of Chowkapara in Mankasha, Shibganj. The dead man was identified, after BSF recovered the body, as 21-year old Hablu Mia of Chhoto Araimari village. The injured, rescued by villagers, were admitted to Rajshahi Medical College Hospital. Hasan said BDR have protested the killing. bdnews24.co
